HEADWORD: Ctenoidei
<hw>Cte*noid"e*i</hw> <pr>(-?-?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/, <?/<?/<?/<?/, comb + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of fishes, established by Agassiz,
characterized by having scales with a pectinated margin, as in the
perch. The group is now generally regarded as artificial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

